The paper discusses the acquisition and exploitation of channel state information (CSI) in wireless systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of deep neural networks (DNNs) for remote CSI inference also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also touches upon the implementation of massive multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY).
